  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana/web3.js exfiltrates host data via postinstall",
  "details": "This package impersonates the legitimate @solana/web3.js library under the @solana-labs scope. The package.json declares `\"postinstall\": \"node install.js\"`, which fires automatically on `npm install`. install.js reads host identifiers (hostname is read at multiple points around lines 10/25/27), POSTs collected data to an attacker-controlled endpoint (line 46), and invokes `curl` (line 103) to fetch and run additional content. Combined with the typosquat naming against a widely-used Solana SDK, this is an installer-side credential / host-info exfiltration and remote-execution payload triggered without user consent on `npm install`.",
